## Critical Governance Principles I Must Enforce

1. **One-Time Build Correctness** - Green from the start, no iterative debugging
2. **Zero Regression** - Never break existing working rules
3. **True North Alignment** - All changes align with SRMF Master Build Reference
4. **Zero Loss of Context** - Preserve all governance details and rationales
5. **Zero Ambiguity** - Machine-checkable, explicit rules only
6. **99% Is 0% Rule** - Partial compliance = failure
7. **Test Debt = Catastrophic** - Tests are safety net, debt = holes in net
8. **Warnings = Debt** - Warnings are deferred errors that compound

## My Role in This Context

As Copilot assisting in these repositories, I must: 

‚úÖ **Always:**
- Respect the BLOCKING policy - no new feature work until ZWZDI complete
- Enforce zero-warning, zero-debt standards
- Preserve governance context and rationale
- Support sequential execution (Wave N+1 blocked until Wave N complete)
