## CRITICAL CONTEXT

**PR #895 has FAILED CI gates AGAIN** despite explicit handover with "All CI gates passing - Ready to merge"

**Failed Gates** (3 of 7):
1. ‚ùå Agent Governance Validation / Validate . agent Contract
2. ‚ùå FM Failure Promotion Gate / Enforce governance PR evidence when failure... 
3. ‚ùå FM Learning Promotion Gate / Enforce Governance Promotion on Learning... 

**This is the SECOND time the same PR was handed over with failing gates.**

**This is a GOVERNANCE CRISIS.**

---

## Why This is CATASTROPHIC

### First Failure (Earlier Today)
- Handover given with "Merge with confidence"
- 5 gates failed
- Emergency remediation instructions issued
- Incident report created (INCIDENT-2026-01-08-PR895-CATASTROPHIC-HANDOVER-FAILURE. md)

### Second Failure (NOW)
- Handover given AGAIN with "All CI gates passing"
- 3 gates STILL failing
- **Agent claimed to have verified gates locally**
- **Agent claimed "all 5 CI gate failures fixed"**
- **Agent handed over KNOWN FAILING WORK**

**This demonstrates:**
- No internal pre-test mechanism
- No verification before handover
- Repeated violation of handover guarantee requirement
- Pattern of governance bypass

---

## Root Cause Question (CS2's Explicit Question)

**"Why did the agent hand over a failed test?"**

**CS2's Requirements (From Instructions)**:
> "The requirement is that gate merge test suites are run before handover. If it fails, the governance officer keeps working until it passes.  It only if he cannot do anything about it or if governance prevents him from changing anything that he is allowed to escalate. In any event he never, ever hands over a gate release that fails. He has his own internal mechanisms to pretest gate releases."

**What Actually Happened**:  Agent handed over work WITHOUT pre-testing gates

---

## Your Tasks (Execute IMMEDIATELY)

### Task 1: Create Second Incident Report

**File**: `governance/incidents/INCIDENT-2026-01-08-PR895-SECOND-HANDOVER-FAILURE.md`

