## Lessons Learned

### Prevention Strategies
**SQLAlchemy**:
- Use SQLAlchemy 2.0 patterns from start
- Import from `sqlalchemy.orm`, not `sqlalchemy.ext.declarative`
- Check deprecation warnings during development

**Pytest Marks**:
- Register all custom marks in `pytest.ini` when created
- Document mark purposes in configuration
- Use `--strict-markers` flag during development

### Recommendations
- Add SQLAlchemy import linting rule
- Add pytest strict-markers to development workflow
- Document mark registration as part of test creation process

