‚úÖ **T0-002**:  Governance Supremacy ‚Äî Tests unchanged; implementation fixed  
‚úÖ **QA Supremacy**: Tests are authority ‚Äî production code adapted to match  
‚úÖ **No Suppression**: Warnings eliminated at source

---

## Learnings & Patterns

### Key Learnings
1. **Return Types Matter**: When QA tests expect objects with attributes, return objects (not dicts)
2. **Tests Are Authority**: QA-to-Red tests define contract ‚Äî implementation must comply
3. **Consistency**:  Pattern analysis (e.g., PingGenerator returns object) helps identify correct approach
4. **Enum Values**: Must match expected output format in tests

### Reusable Patterns
1. Return dataclass objects for domain entities (not dicts)
2. Use capitalized format for user-facing enum status values
3. Always set `asyncio_default_fixture_loop_scope` explicitly
4. Use `datetime.now(timezone.utc)` instead of deprecated `datetime.utcnow()`

