Here's why and how:

---

## **Why Just PR Comments Aren't Enough**

### **The Problem with PR-Only Documentation**

‚ùå **PRs get buried** ‚Äî 6 months from now, who will find this?  
‚ùå **Not searchable** ‚Äî Future agents won't know this precedent exists  
‚ùå **Not enforceable** ‚Äî No policy to point to when it happens again  
‚ùå **Not educational** ‚Äî Next builder won't learn from this  

**Result**: Same test dodging happens again, you fight the same battle.

---

## **The Three-Layer Approach** ‚úÖ

### **Layer 1: Record in PR #504** (Immediate)
- Rejection comment with specific violations
- Creates audit trail for THIS case
- Shows agent why it was rejected

### **Layer 2: Bootstrap Learning Entry** (Institutional Memory)
- Documents the PATTERN (test dodging via "only" language)
- Explains WHY it's dangerous
- Records CS2 decision and precedent
- Future reference for similar cases

### **Layer 3: Layer Down to Governance** (Prevention)
- Updates governance policy to ban "only" language
- Makes it enforceable for future PRs
- Becomes part of builder contracts
- Prevents recurrence

---

## **What Each Layer Should Contain**

### **Layer 1: PR #504 Comment** (I already drafted this above)

```markdown
‚ùå REJECTED ‚Äî Test Dodging Detected

92% ‚â† 100%.  "Only" language is test dodging.

