description:  |
    # ZWZDI Campaign ‚Äî Prevention Phase

    **Phase**: Prevention (Governance Policy Update & Postmortem)
    **Campaign**: ZWZDI-2026-001
    **Duration**:  1 day
    **Assignee**: FM (Foreman)

    ---

    ## Objective

    Review lessons learned from the ZWZDI campaign, update governance policies, and implement systematic prevention against future warning and test debt accumulation. 

    ## Responsibilities

    1. **Governance Policy Update**
       - Review Bootstrap Learning entries from Verification phase
       - Update all relevant governance documents (GOVERNANCE_LEARNING_BRIEF.md, PLANNING_PHASE_COMPLETION_SUMMARY.md, team onboarding material, builder contracts)
       - Apply new policies from rejection patterns, only-language ban, test dodging, etc.
       - Announce updated policies to all contributors/builders

    2. **Postmortem & Debt Prevention Plan**
       - Document ZWZDI campaign lessons in Bootstrap Learning
       - Identify root causes of warning/test debt emergence
       - Update risk mitigation protocols and campaign structure
       - Specify technical/process gates to prevent future regression (e.g., zero-warning merge gate, PR language linting, builder training)

    3. **Verification of Policy Implementation**
       - Audit updated documents, onboardings, PR templates, code review checklists to ensure new governance embedded everywhere

    ---

    ## Output

    - [ ] Updated governance files (commit references or attach drafts)
    - [ ] Prevention protocols/checklist
    - [ ] Bootstrap/postmortem report
    - [ ] List of risks and countermeasures
    - [ ] Approvals/announcements logged

    ---

    ## Success Criteria

    - [ ] All policy updates applied in all relevant places
    - [ ] Team is aware of all new prevention policies
