# ‚úÖ APPROVED ‚Äî POLICY-NO-ONLY-LANGUAGE Created (Test Dodging Prevention)

**PR**:  #901  
**Issue**: Closes #900  
**Authority**: CS2 Decision 2026-01-08  
**Trigger**: PR APGI-cmy/maturion-foreman-office-app#504 test dodging incident  
**Status**: ‚úÖ **READY TO MERGE**

---

## Summary

Complete governance policy package banning minimizing language (\"only\", \"just\", \"minor\", \"non-blocking\") when describing test failures or technical debt. 

**Enforces**: 100% GREEN mandate ‚Äî no partial credit, no minimizing, no test dodging. 

---

## Files Created/Modified (7 files, 1,412 lines)

### Core Policy Document ‚úÖ
**`governance/policy/POLICY-NO-ONLY-LANGUAGE.md`** (545 lines)

Complete policy establishing: 
- **Banned language**: \"only\", \"just\", \"minor\", \"non-blocking\", \"trivial\", \"good enough\", \"future refinement\"
- **Required language**: \"100% tests passing\" or \"NOT READY - X tests failing\"
- **Enforcement**: Automatic rejection, no exceptions without CS2 pre-approval
- **Rationale**: Slippery slope, historical evidence (365 warnings), subjective judgment problem
- **Precedent**: PR #504 rejection with full case study
- **Examples**: Rejected vs. approved PR descriptions

**15 comprehensive sections** covering:
1. Purpose and constitutional authority
2. Policy statement and banned language
3. Rationale (slippery slope, 365 warnings case study)
4. Enforcement rules (automatic rejection)
5. Examples (rejected vs. approved PRs)
6. Precedent (PR #504 case study)
7. Related policies (BUILD_PHILOSOPHY, QA_POLICY_MASTER, T0-003)
8. Training requirements
9. Governance ripple instructions
10. Updates/amendments process
11. Compliance monitoring
12. Builder acknowledgment

---

