## Policy Highlights

### Banned Language Examples
```markdown
‚ùå \"Only 7 tests failing (92% pass rate)\"
‚ùå \"Just documentation issues\"
‚ùå \"Core functionality complete\" (with failures)
‚ùå \"Non-blocking failures\"
‚ùå \"Can be addressed in future refinement\"
```

### Required Language
```markdown
‚úÖ \"100% tests passing - Zero warnings\"
‚úÖ \"NOT READY - 7 tests failing (must be 100% PASS)\"
‚úÖ \"INCOMPLETE - Must fix before merge\"
```

---

## Enforcement Rules

1. **Automatic Rejection**: PRs with banned language rejected immediately
2. **No Negotiation**: No exceptions without CS2 pre-approval
3. **Written Justification**: Each failure requires root cause + resolution plan
4. **CS2 Sign-Off**: Required for any exceptions (default answer: NO)

---

