## @APGI-cmy

You honestly are not getting it if I place this after full doctine. there is no .md in the file, only yaml. The frontmatter that provides like a summary fo the agent is frontmatter and this should be followed by .md. The way the frontmatter sits betwee --- and --- if you add it like --- the entire contents of the file --- the entire contents of the file is frontmatter and ther is no .md part in the file

## Copilot

## üí° **AH!  I GET IT NOW! **

You're absolutely right! I was confusing things. Let me clarify:

---

## **The Problem**

Your governance file currently has: 

```yaml
---
name: governance-liaison
description: ... 
instructions: |
  [ALL your detailed content is HERE inside instructions]
---
```

This makes the **entire detailed content part of the YAML frontmatter** (inside the `instructions` field). There's **no markdown section at all** after the frontmatter.

---

## **What It SHOULD Be**

Like the FM file:

```yaml
---
name: governance-liaison
description: FM-repository-scoped governance alignment agent (SHORT SUMMARY)
---

# GOVERNANCE LIAISON (FM REPO) ‚Äî MINIMAL CONTRACT

[All your detailed content as MARKDOWN here, NOT in the YAML]

**Version**: 2.0.0 | **Date**: 2026-01-08 | **Status**: Active

## Authority & Mission
... 
[rest of content]
```

---

## **The Fix**

**Step 1**: Keep the frontmatter SHORT (just metadata)

```yaml
---
name: governance-liaison
description: FM-repository-scoped governance alignment agent.  Ensures FM repository compliance with corporate governance, agent behavior doctrine, PR gate philosophy, escalation protocols, FM readiness.  Operates ONLY in FM repository. 
---
```

**Step 2**: Everything else goes AFTER the closing `---` as regular markdown

```markdown
# GOVERNANCE LIAISON (FM REPO) ‚Äî MINIMAL CONTRACT

**Version**: 2.0.0 | **Date**: 2026-01-08 | **Status**: Active

## Authority & Mission

Corporate governance canon in **maturion-foreman-governance**... 
[etc]
```

---

## **So the structure is**: 

```
---
[short metadata]
---
[ALL your detailed content as markdown]
```

**NOT**:

```
---
[short metadata]
instructions: |
  [all content crammed in here]
---
```

---

**Does that make sense now?** The frontmatter should be BRIEF metadata only, then close with `---`, then your full contract content comes after as regular markdown. 

