## Files to Up-Ripple

### 1. POLICY-NO-ONLY-LANGUAGE (NEW)

**Source**: `maturion-foreman-office-app/governance/policies/POLICY-NO-ONLY-LANGUAGE.md`  
**Destination**: `maturion-foreman-governance/governance/policies/POLICY-NO-ONLY-LANGUAGE.md`

**Why Canonical**:
- Enforces T0-002 (Governance Supremacy Rule ‚Äî "99% is 0%")
- Enforces T0-003 (Zero Test Debt Constitutional Rule)
- Universal applicability (all builders, all repos)
- Constitutional precedence (bans minimizing language universally)

**Content Summary**:
- Bans:  "only", "just", "minor", "non-blocking" when describing failures
- Requires: "100% tests passing" OR "NOT READY - X failing"
- Enforcement:  Automatic rejection, CS2 exception only
- Rationale: Minimizing language enables test dodging

---

### 2. BOOTSTRAP-TEST-DODGING-001 (NEW)

**Source**: `maturion-foreman-office-app/bootstrap/learnings/BOOTSTRAP-TEST-DODGING-001.md`  
**Destination**: `maturion-foreman-governance/bootstrap/learnings/BOOTSTRAP-TEST-DODGING-001.md`

**Why Canonical**:
- Documents universal pattern (test dodging via language)
- Provides case study for all builder training
- Establishes permanent learning (BL-021)
- Supports POLICY-NO-ONLY-LANGUAGE enforcement

**Content Summary**:
- PR #504 incident (92% pass rate claimed as "COMPLETE")
- Root cause:  Minimizing language masked 8% failure rate
- Prevention: POLICY-NO-ONLY-LANGUAGE enacted
- Learning: "Only" is the universal language of test dodging

---

### 3. BL-021 Entry (NEW)

**Source**: `maturion-foreman-office-app/BOOTSTRAP_EXECUTION_LEARNINGS.md` (BL-021 section)  
**Destination**: `maturion-foreman-governance/BOOTSTRAP_EXECUTION_LEARNINGS.md`

**Content**:  Register BL-021 in canonical learning registry

**Learning Statement**:
> "Minimizing language ('only', 'just', 'minor', 'non-blocking') MUST be banned when describing test failures, warnings, or technical debt. Such language enables test dodging by normalizing incomplete work."

---

