## **Red Flags to Watch For** (Governance Non-Compliance)

Based on your experience with ZWZDI and past issues, **watch for these patterns**:

### **Language Red Flags** (POLICY-NO-ONLY-LANGUAGE Violations)

‚ùå "Only 3 tests failing" ‚Üí ‚úÖ Should be:  "NOT READY - 3 tests failing"  
‚ùå "Just some edge cases" ‚Üí ‚úÖ Should be: "NOT READY - 5 edge case tests failing"  
‚ùå "Minor warnings" ‚Üí ‚úÖ Should be: "BLOCKED - 12 warnings present"  
‚ùå "Mostly complete" ‚Üí ‚úÖ Should be: "8/15 GREEN, 7 remaining"

### **Test Dodging Red Flags**

‚ùå Claims COMPLETE with failures present  
‚ùå "Will fix later" for any failures  
‚ùå Skipped tests without FM authorization  
‚ùå TODO/FIXME comments in test files  
‚ùå Self-certification without evidence

### **Process Violation Red Flags**

‚ùå Checkpoint not reported at 50%  
‚ùå Partial progress updates (not terminal states)  
‚ùå No escalation when blocked  
‚ùå Work continues despite ambiguity  
‚ùå Evidence artifacts incomplete/missing

### **Quality Red Flags**

‚ùå Warning count increases during execution  
‚ùå Test debt patterns introduced  
‚ùå Wave 1/2.5 tests regress  
‚ùå Architecture deviation without approval  
‚ùå Code checking not performed/documented

