````yaml type="draft-issue"
type: draft-issue
tag:  "mandatory-process-improvement-reflection-governance-2026-01-08"
issueNumber: 0
repository: "APGI-cmy/maturion-foreman-governance"
state:  "draft"
title: "Require Compulsory Process Improvement Reflection (Not Just Feature Enhancements) in All Builder Agent Contracts"
description: "## Problem\n\nCurrent Maturion builder contracts (e.g., `.github/agents/api-builder.md`, `.github/agents/ForemanApp-agent. md`) require builders to provide *product* enhancements at the end of each deliverable, i.e., features or architectural upgrades marked as \"PARKED.\" However, they do **not** explicitly require a compulsory *process improvement reflection* per build, leading to lost governance insight, missed learning opportunities, and stagnated builder discipline.\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\n- ZWZDI closure and subsequent Wave 2.0 rollouts surfaced the necessity for builders to self-report **process improvements** beyond feature upgrades (e.g., \"what failed in this build and what would prevent recurrence?\")\n- In PR APGI-cmy/maturion-foreman-office-app#517, the builder's enhancement section included only feature suggestions, not any reflection on process, workflow, governance compliance, or automation/tooling gaps.\n- This is a governance gap: without process-oriented reflection, we cannot close systematic test escapes, missed checkpoints, or build-to-green cycle violations.\n- This gap also precludes recording those lessons as bootstrap learnings across builds.\n\n---\n\n## Required Updates\n\n### 1. Builder Agent Contracts (All Repos, Tier-0 Alignment)\n- **MANDATE:** Every builder agent contract (e.g., api-builder, qa-builder, UI-builder, etc.) must require a process improvement reflection in each builder completion report.\n- **Reflection scope:** Minimum set of mandatory questions:\n    - What went well in this build?\n    - What was blocked or failed and what caused it?\n    - What governance or contract/process gaps were exposed?\n    - What should be improved (CI, process, contracts, requirements, design, communication, tooling, scheduling, etc.) before the next wave/iteration?\n    - Did the builder comply with all governance learning/lessons (BL-016, BL-018, BL-019, BL-022, etc.)? If not, why?\n- **Prohibit** \"None identified\" unless each question above is answered and explicitly justified.\n- Process improvement recommendations must be traceable for bootstrap learning registration.\n\n### 2. Bootstrap Learning Tracking\n- When process improvement reflections reveal governance gaps or systematic failures, a **BL entry** must be registered in governance/canon/BOOTSTRAP_EXECUTION_LEARNINGS.md.\n\n### 3. Layer-Down Requirement\n- All downstream agent contracts (.github/agents/*) must reference this new requirement, and FM must enforce provision of process improvement reflection before GATE COMPLETE.\n\n---\n\n## Rationale\n\n- Builders only suggesting future features in enhancement reflection is insufficient.\n- Repetitive build flaws and stalling root causes are not captured/corrected without compulsory process self-reflection.\n- True governance discipline requires continuous, explicit improvement cycles.\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] All builder agent contracts (canonical + application repo) updated to include above process improvement reflection mandate\n- [ ] Sample completion report template/tooling updated to require process improvement\n- [ ] BL tracking structure recognizes process improvement learnings\n- [ ] FM contract specifies GATE requires both feature AND process improvement reflection before marking any builder issue COMPLETE\n\n---\n\n**Authority**: CS2 (Johan Ras), ZWZDI lessons, Wave 2.0 execution failures\n\n---\n  "
labels: ["governance", "process-improvement", "bootstrap-learning", "tier-0"]
````

